<br>
Maybe the msg is intended to name the first PC or PET hit by the MOB. So when mez wore off, it hit the pet, cuasing the pet to hit back, causing the msg that Pet_01 awakened mob_b<br>
<br>
My reason for thinking this is because I was still receiving the msg from my pet, &quot;I am unable to wake mob_b&quot; before I will see the msg, &quot;Pet_01 awakened Mob_01.&quot;<br>
<br>
Since the original patch  “not allowing pets to break mez”  I have noticed times where it looks like my pet keeps breaking mez, but if u look at the log you will see a round of attacks from the mob on the pet first in every case. The best way to prevent this is by doing the following.<br>
<br>
Let's say 2 mobs are inc, MA is on mob_a and my pet is on mob_b. When my pet is engaged in a fight, I can still give him orders to attack mob_a. Once mob_b is dead or mezzed my pet will leave mob_b and go directly to mob_a.  <br>
<br>
For best results, adds must not be in range to still attack my pet.<br>
<br>
If I don’t give my pet the order to attack mob_a, he will just sit there with his thumb up his ass till I tell him what to do or till he is hit again. <br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
