<br>
Use pet hold everytime the mob your pet was fighting die, and in any case where you have any doubts about pet aggroing the wrong target (AoE stunning mobs in VT for example).<br>
<br>
Use back off everytime you need to clear your pets aggro (if he gets hit by a target that has been mezed for example) to prevent pet switching target. Back off followed by attack will make sure pet is only aggro on his curent target.<br>
<br>
And of course use assist to pick targets and keep pet on hold at all time when not fighting (you never know what's gonna be pulled next).<br>
<br>
